    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Traditional foliate and vegetal arabesques in the Turkish Ottoman decorative style dating from the 15th century. The pattern depicts long, pointed split-leaves with curved sides and prehensile tips, often tightly strung together with classical vines.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
